  "text": "Approximate simulation methods can be implemented to reduce the computational resources required for Monte Carlo simulation. In short, the dynamics of a chosen biochemical reaction network are simplified so that fewer computational resources are required to simulate each sample path. Examples of such approximation schemes include the widely-used tau-leap [CITATION_1] , and Rleap [CITATION_2] methods. We discuss both the tau-and R-leap methods in turn.",
